==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: paca
<hw>pa"ca</hw> <pr>(Pg. p⟦aum⟧"k⟦adot⟧; E. p⟦amac⟧"k⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg., from the native name.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large burrowing South American rodent
(<spn>Agouti paca</spn> syn. <spn>Cuniculus paca</spn>, formerly
<spn>C⟦oe⟧logenys paca</spn>), having blackish brown fur, with four
parallel rows of white spots along its sides; the spotted cavy. It is
closely allied to the agouti and the Guinea pig and is highly esteemed
as food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pacable</ent>⟦br⟧
